title: Wireless MFCJ5330DW MFCJ5830DW or MFCJ5930DW install - Macintosh®
description:
Learn how to set up your Brother MFC-J5330DW, MFC-J5830DW, or MFC-J5930DW inkjet all-in-one printer on a wireless network in this tutorial.

The model shown is the MFCJ5830DW

Models covered: 
Brother MFCJ5330DW 
Brother MFCJ5830DW 
Brother MFCJ5830DWXL
Brother MFCJ5930DW 

This video is for Macintosh users, for the Windows version click: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=yy_cbVXlheY

For more videos, tutorials, and FAQs visit our support site at: http://www.brother-usa.com/support

Brother – at your side

Quick Links / Table of Contents:
Models Covered 00:09
Required Information 00:19
Custom SSID and Network Key 00:47
Setup Wizard on the Printer 01:04:00
Insert or Download the software 02:01
Running the Installer software 2:10
Enter your password 02:57
Enter a Scan To name 03:13
CUPS driver 03:30
More resources at brother-usa.com 03:53



Today we’re going to walk through the wireless setup of your Brother MFC-J5830DW inkjet printer.

This video will cover multiple models and operating systems. Even though your machine may not match the model on the screen, the overall process will be the same. (Covers MFC-J5330DW and MFC-J5930DW network setup too.)

For more Tutorials, FAQ's and Videos, visit us at www.brother-usa.com

Thank you for choosing Brother
